The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Durban, Sept. 7 (PTI): A 56-year-old man, his wife and their son were found dead with their throats slit at their home in the city early yesterday.           
	Police said four robbers trussed Naren Sham, Meer and Kavir before killing them. Then they broke the safe and fled with jewellery, cash and other valuables. The domestic worker, who too was bound, later escaped and alerted the security guard.                   
	 Mumbai (PTI): The son of Mustafa Dossa, an accused in the 1993 Bombay blasts, has been arrested in an extortion case along with an associate, police said on Sunday. They had threatened to kill a person who had borrowed Rs 75,000 from Dossas son.                   
	 Hyderabad (PTI): Two dacoits escaped with four boxes containing gold ornaments worth Rs 1.11 crore from the cargo zone of Rajiv Gandhi International Airport, police said. The four boxes had been brought from Mumbai by a courier service firm.                  
	 Bhopal (PTI): Fire broke out at a Bhopal hotel from its kitchen around 1.30pm on Sunday. It was soon controlled, but the thick smoke spread across the hotel and caused panic among guests and staff, police said.                  
	 Pune (PTI): Former Maharashtra minister Dharmarao Baba Atram has been charged with killing two chinkaras and two rabbits. He was initially accused of killing one chinkara. The public prosecutor claimed that the hunt was a pre-planned expedition.                                                                                                                         
